"title": "6641: election, responsibilities of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6641: election, responsibilities of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's election lays responsibilities upon those who have been chosen. Election to salvation has the natural consequence of election to service.</p>\n<h2>Election to leadership</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer1:5\">JER 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:2-Judg13:5\">JDG 13:2–13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:26\">PSA 105:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:23\">PSA 106:23</a></p>\n<h2>Election to religious service</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:5\">DEU 21:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:3-Deut18:5\">DEU 18:3–18:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:27-1Sam2:28\">1SA 2:27–2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:2\">1CH 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:11\">2CH 29:11</a></p>\n<h2>Election to build the house of God</h2>\n<h3>Election to build the tabernacle</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:2-Exod31:5\">EXO 31:2–31:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:30-Exod35:33\">EXO 35:30–35:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:6-Exod31:11\">EXO 31:6–31:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod35:34-Exod36:2\">EXO 35:34–36:2</a></p>\n<h3>Election to build the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:6\">1CH 28:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:10\">1CH 28:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:1\">1CH 29:1</a></p>\n<h2>Election of foreign kings as instruments of discipline</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1\">ISA 45:1</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:28\">ISA 44:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:14-Isa48:15\">ISA 48:14–48:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:17\">ISA 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:20\">ISA 7:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:9\">JER 25:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer27:6\">JER 27:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer43:10\">JER 43:10</a></p>\n<h2>Election to kingship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:4\">1CH 28:4</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1-1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:1–16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:71\">PSA 78:70–78:71</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps89:3-Ps89:4\">PSA 89:3–89:4</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:20-1Sam10:24\">1SA 10:20–10:24</a> <em>Saul</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:5-1Chr28:7\">1CH 28:5–28:7</a> <em>Solomon</em></p>\n<h2>Election of the Messiah</h2>\n<h3>The OT predicts the coming of a ``chosen one''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:7\">ISA 42:1–42:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6-Isa9:7\">ISA 9:6–9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:5-Isa49:7\">ISA 49:5–49:7</a></p>\n<h3>The NT identifies Jesus Christ as God's chosen Messiah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:35\">LUK 9:35</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:16-Matt3:17\">MAT 3:16–3:17</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:15-Matt12:21\">MAT 12:15–12:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:4\">ISA 42:1–42:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:21\">1PE 1:18–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:4-1Pet2:6\">1PE 2:4–2:6</a></p>\n<h2>Election to apostleship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:13-Luke6:16\">LUK 6:13–6:16</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:14-Mark3:19\">MRK 3:14–3:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:70\">JHN 6:70</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:18\">JHN 13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:19\">JHN 15:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:2\">ACT 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:26\">ACT 1:21–1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:15-Acts9:16\">ACT 9:15–9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:14-Acts22:15\">ACT 22:14–22:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:1\">ROM 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:1\">1CO 1:1</a></p>",
